{{Quote|All ships, this is General Bel Iblis. We've just been informed that a strong Frezhlix force is moving on the Sif'krie homeworld of Sif'kric.|[[Garm Bel Iblis/Legends|Garm Bel Iblis]]|<ref name="Specter of the Past">''[[Specter of the Past]]''</ref>}}
The '''Sif'krie''', from the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Sif'kric]] in the [[Sif'kric system/Legends|Sif'kric system]], had an economy based on the export of the highly perishable and valuable [[pommwomm]] plants. They shared their system with the [[Frezh]]lix, who began feuding with them as soon as the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] pulled out. They had a [[Sif'krie government|government]].

In [[19 ABY/Legends|19 ABY]], when a Frezhlix fleet [[Blockade of Sif'kric|blockaded]] their system, up to 20% of their yearly planetary income was at risk of being wiped out. The stated motivation of the Frezhlix was to make the Sif'krie reconsider their position on the [[Caamas Document]] in their [[sector assembly]], thus making their [[Sector/Legends|sector]] support the [[Drashtine Initiative]] in the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] [[New Republic Senate/Legends|Senate]] and its demand for punishment of the [[Bothan/Legends|Bothans]]. Though the Sif'krie were unable to put a formal request for military aid through, the New Republic forces commanded by [[Garm Bel Iblis/Legends|Garm Bel Iblis]] and [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]] arrived to investigate anyway. When the Frezhlix fired on New Republic [[T-65 X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-wings]] who had broken through their lines (supposedly to investigate smugglers), the New Republic returned fire, and defeated the blockading fleet.

With the Frezhlix threat eliminated, the Sif'krie felt secure enough to bolster the pro-Bothan forces helping to defend [[Bothawui/Legends|Bothawui]]. Sif'krie skiffs fought alongside the [[Diamal]]a-led fleet, and later the New Republic coalition, at a [[Battle of Bothawui (Galactic Civil War)|battle at Bothawui]].

